eland.elections/index.html">http://edition.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/europe/04/25/iceland.elections/index.html</a></li><li id="cite_note-1"><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">↑</a> <a class="external text" href="http://www.thjodfundur2010.is/other_files/2010/doc/Act-on-a-Constitutional-Assembly.pdf" rel="nofollow" title="http://www.thjodfundur2010.is/other_files/2010/doc/Act-on-a-Constitutional-Assembly.pdf">Act</a> on a Constitutional Assembly no. 90/2010, Article 20 and Interim Provision</li><li id="cite_note-2"><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">↑</a> Alda Sigmundsdottir, <a class="external text" href="http://www.usatoday.com/money/world/2011-06-12-Iceland-constitution-online_n.htm" rel="nofollow" title="http://www.usatoday.com/money/world/2011-06-12-Iceland-constitution-online_n.htm">Associated Press</a> (12/6/2011)</li><li id="cite_note-3"><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">↑</a> Stjornlagarad.is. “A Bill Submitted to Althinghi”</li><li id="cite_note-4"><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">↑</a> Article 3 of the Constitutional Act</li><li id="cite_note-5"><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">↑</a> Helga Kristin Einarsdottir, “Iceland’s Ruling Coalition Splits Following Protests” <a class="external free" href="http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&amp;sid=avntV39aM_7I&amp;refer=europe" rel="nofollow" title="http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&amp;sid=avntV39aM_7I&amp;refer=europe">http://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&amp;sid=avntV39aM_7I&amp;refer=europe</a> [DEAD LINK]</li><li id="cite_note-6"><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">↑</a> Interview with Gudjon Mar Gudjonsson on <a class="external text" href="http://ohmygov.com/blogs/general_news/archive/2009/11/13/in-iceland-trying-to-reprogram-government.aspx" rel="nofollow" title="http://ohmygov.com/blogs/general_news/archive/2009/11/13/in-iceland-trying-to-reprogram-government.aspx">OhMyGov.com</a> [DEAD LINK]</li><li id="cite_note-7"><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">↑</a> <a class="external text" href="http